 area = (ulong)width * height;\n+\n+        if (width == 0 || height == 0)\n+        {\n+            throw new InvalidDataException($\"Image '{path}' has invalid dimensions {width}x{height}.\");","path":"src/PrivatePdfConverter/Services/FileService.cs","commit_id":"aafeb7a8b245483e755469a7b0a6fe5c7e27f69c","original_commit_id":"aafeb7a8b245483e755469a7b0a6fe5c7e27f69c","user":{"login":"jurczewski","id":24575781,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0NTc1Nzgx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/24575781?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski","html_url":"https://github.com/jurczewski","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jurczewski/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"Using **InvalidDataException** here for a predictable validation case feels like using exceptions for control flow. Cases like “image too large” are expected validation failures, not unexpected runtime errors.\n\nBecause of that, both **ImgToPdf** and **DirToPdf** need nearly identical try/catch blocks just to log and return, which makes the flow harder to follow.\n\nIt would be cleaner to handle `LogError`/`LogCritical` directly inside `LoadValidatedImage`, return `MagickImage?`, and return null when validation fails. Then callers can simply do:\n\n```csharp\nvar image = FileService.LoadValidatedImage(path);\nif (image is null) return;\n\nimages.